#: src/advice.md:1
msgid "Other style advice"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:3
msgid "Expressions"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:5
msgid "Prefer to use Rust's expression oriented nature where possible;"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:8
msgid "// use\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:9
msgid "// not\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:19
msgid "Names"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:21
msgid "Types shall be `UpperCamelCase`,"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:22
msgid "Enum variants shall be `UpperCamelCase`,"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:23
msgid "Struct fields shall be `snake_case`,"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:24
msgid "Function and method names shall be `snake_case`,"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:25
msgid "Local variables shall be `snake_case`,"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:26
msgid "Macro names shall be `snake_case`,"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:27
msgid ""
"Constants (`const`s and immutable `static`s) shall be `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`."
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:28
msgid ""
"When a name is forbidden because it is a reserved word (such as `crate`), "
"either use a raw identifier (`r#crate`) or use a trailing underscore "
"(`crate_`). Don't misspell the word (`krate`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:32
msgid "Modules"
msgstr ""

#: src/advice.md:34
msgid "Avoid `#[path]` annotations where possible."
msgstr ""
